[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ipswich deaf blind man pushed on to tracks at Chelmsford station

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
CCTV footage of a deaf blind man being pushed on to the tracks during an attack at a railway station has been released by British Transport Police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
24 October 2014 Last updated at 17:35 BST
The 31-year-old man, from Ipswich, was punched as he tried to get back on to the platform at Chelmsford station in Essex in February.
Two men have been jailed for the assault on the man and his brother at Chelmsford Crown Court.
